\\nAlso, do I need to check the checkstyle line length, likely 120? The placeholder test may not be necessary and could be replaced or deleted to improve the active class.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating test structure**\\\\n\\\\nI’m looking at the placeholder test, which currently covers only one coordinate test. While I could leave it as is, it seems pretty useless. I might consider editing the placeholder to make it public since top-level test classes need to be public anyway, but that would violate existing conventions. I wonder if I should modify it to better align with the testing structure or replace it entirely. It seems like there should be a better approach here.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating test class structure**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether all top-level test classes should be public. If I keep a placeholder file, it might violate this rule, but maybe I could edit it to be public. The placeholder content doesn't seem meaningful, so should I replace it with a simple smoke test? But I want to avoid duplicating coverage, especially since the existing placeholder isn't dynamic. Deleting the placeholder might be the best option to prevent issues.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing class and test structure**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether deleting unrelated placeholders will improve quality. I can use bash to remove them, but I need to ensure that the tests don't require direct reflection. Using `getClass()` seems acceptable, and I might assert the logger's instance type to validate the adapter class without needing to reflect implementation details. Importing `Log4jLoggerAdapter` and asserting that might work too, but I have to be cautious of triggering dynamic behavior. Overall, I’m trying to strike a balance between clean code and effective testing.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying logging tests**\\\\n\\\\nI’m noticing that the class is public final, yet it has a package-private constructor. I can use `assertThat(logger).isInstanceOf(Log4jLoggerAdapter.class)`, as it references the class without initializing it, which is good. This might not violate the public API since it pertains to the active class. Now, I need to ensure that the logging is exercised properly. I should familiarize myself with the `AppenderSkeleton` methods like `getLevel`, `getRenderedMessage`, `getLoggerName`, and `getThrowableInformation().getThrowable()`.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_0yEzydyNrsGdLuX6FD8pvQLj|fc_080194adfb1420f20169f9b22d61ec81a0b64cf1324d82a589\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_log4j12/Log4jLoggerAdapterTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_slf4j.slf4j_log4j12;\\n\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\\nimport org.apache.log4j.Appender;\\nimport org.apache.log4j.AppenderSkeleton;\\nimport org.apache.log4j.Level;\\nimport org.apache.log4j.LogManager;\\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.LoggingEvent;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\\nimport org.slf4j.impl.Log4jLoggerAdapter;\\nimport org.slf4j.spi.LocationAwareLogger;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class Log4jLoggerAdapterTest {\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void loggerFactoryCreatesAdapterAndForwardsFormattedMessagesToLog4j() {\\n        try (TestLoggerContext context = TestLoggerContext.create(\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-standard\\\")) {\\n            org.slf4j.Logger logger = context.slf4jLogger();\\n            IllegalStateException failure = new IllegalStateException(\\\"boom\\\");\\n\\n            logger.trace(\\\"trace {}\\\", \\\"message\\\");\\n            logger.info(\\\"info {} {}\\\", new Object[]{\\\"first\\\", \\\"second\\\"});\\n            logger.error(\\\"error message\\\", failure);\\n\\n            List<LoggingEvent> events = context.events();\\n\\n            assertThat(logger).isInstanceOf(Log4jLoggerAdapter.class);\\n            assertThat(logger.getName()).isEqualTo(\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-standard\\\");\\n            assertThat(events).hasSize(3);\\n            assertThat(events).extracting(LoggingEvent::getLevel)\\n                    .containsExactly(Level.TRACE, Level.INFO, Level.ERROR);\\n            assertThat(events).extracting(LoggingEvent::getRenderedMessage)\\n                    .containsExactly(\\\"trace message\\\", \\\"info first second\\\", \\\"error message\\\");\\n            assertThat(events).extracting(LoggingEvent::getLoggerName)\\n                    .containsOnly(\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-standard\\\");\\n            assertThat(events.get(2).getThrowableInformation().getThrowable()).isSameAs(failure);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void locationAwareLoggingMapsSlf4jLevelsToLog4jLevels() {\\n        try (TestLoggerContext context = TestLoggerContext.create(\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-location-aware\\\")) {\\n            LocationAwareLogger logger = (LocationAwareLogger) context.slf4jLogger();\\n            IllegalArgumentException failure = new IllegalArgumentException(\\\"warn\\\");\\n\\n            logger.log(null, LocationAwareInvoker.class.getName(), LocationAwareLogger.WARN_INT,\\n                    \\\"warn message\\\", null, failure);\\n\\n            assertThat(context.events()).singleElement().satisfies(event -> {\\n                assertThat(event.getLevel()).isEqualTo(Level.WARN);\\n                assertThat(event.getRenderedMessage()).isEqualTo(\\\"warn message\\\");\\n                assertThat(event.getThrowableInformation().getThrowable()).isSameAs(failure);\\n                assertThat(event.getFQNOfLoggerClass()).isEqualTo(LocationAwareInvoker.class.getName());\\n            });\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class TestLoggerContext implements AutoCloseable {\\n\\n        private final org.apache.log4j.Logger log4jLogger;\\n        private final Level previousLevel;\\n        private final boolean previousAdditivity;\\n        private final List<Appender> previousAppenders;\\n        private final RecordingAppender appender;\\n        private final org.slf4j.Logger slf4jLogger;\\n\\n        private TestLoggerContext(String loggerName) {\\n            this.log4jLogger = LogManager.getLogger(loggerName);\\n            this.previousLevel = this.log4jLogger.getLevel();\\n            this.previousAdditivity = this.log4jLogger.getAdditivity();\\n            this.previousAppenders = currentAppenders(this.log4jLogger);\\n            this.appender = new RecordingAppender();\\n\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAllAppenders();\\n            this.log4jLogger.setAdditivity(false);\\n            this.log4jLogger.setLevel(Level.TRACE);\\n            this.log4jLogger.addAppender(this.appender);\\n            this.slf4jLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(loggerName);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static TestLoggerContext create(String loggerName) {\\n            return new TestLoggerContext(loggerName);\\n        }\\n\\n        private org.slf4j.Logger slf4jLogger() {\\n            return this.slf4jLogger;\\n        }\\n\\n        private List<LoggingEvent> events() {\\n            return List.copyOf(this.appender.events);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void close() {\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAppender(this.appender);\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAllAppenders();\\n            for (Appender previousAppender : this.previousAppenders) {\\n                this.log4jLogger.addAppender(previousAppender);\\n            }\\n            this.log4jLogger.setLevel(this.previousLevel);\\n            this.log4jLogger.setAdditivity(this.previousAdditivity);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static List<Appender> currentAppenders(org.apache.log4j.Logger logger) {\\n            List<Appender> appenders = new ArrayList<>();\\n            Enumeration<?> allAppenders = logger.getAllAppenders();\\n            while (allAppenders.hasMoreElements()) {\\n                appenders.add((Appender) allAppenders.nextElement());\\n            }\\n            return appenders;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class RecordingAppender extends AppenderSkeleton {\\n\\n        private final List<LoggingEvent> events = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected void append(LoggingEvent event) {\\n            this.events.add(event);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public boolean requiresLayout() {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void close() {\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class LocationAwareInvoker {\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_log4j12/Log4jLoggerAdapterTest.java\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\\\n */\\\\npackage org_slf4j.slf4j_log4j12;\\\\n\\\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\\\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\\\\nimport java.util.List;\\\\n\\\\nimport org.apache.log4j.Appender;\\\\nimport org.apache.log4j.AppenderSkeleton;\\\\nimport org.apache.log4j.Level;\\\\nimport org.apache.log4j.LogManager;\\\\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.LoggingEvent;\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\\\nimport org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\\\\nimport org.slf4j.impl.Log4jLoggerAdapter;\\\\nimport org.slf4j.spi.LocationAwareLogger;\\\\n\\\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\\\n\\\\npublic class Log4jLoggerAdapterTest {\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void loggerFactoryCreatesAdapterAndForwardsFormattedMessagesToLog4j() {\\\\n        try (TestLoggerContext context = TestLoggerContext.create(\\\\\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-standard\\\\\\\")) {\\\\n            org.slf4j.Logger logger = context.slf4jLogger();\\\\n            IllegalStateException failure = new IllegalStateException(\\\\\\\"boom\\\\\\\");\\\\n\\\\n            logger.trace(\\\\\\\"trace {}\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\");\\\\n            logger.info(\\\\\\\"info {} {}\\\\\\\", new Object[]{\\\\\\\"first\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"second\\\\\\\"});\\\\n            logger.error(\\\\\\\"error message\\\\\\\", failure);\\\\n\\\\n            List<LoggingEvent> events = context.events();\\\\n\\\\n            assertThat(logger).isInstanceOf(Log4jLoggerAdapter.class);\\\\n            assertThat(logger.getName()).isEqualTo(\\\\\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-standard\\\\\\\");\\\\n            assertThat(events).hasSize(3);\\\\n            assertThat(events).extracting(LoggingEvent::getLevel)\\\\n                    .containsExactly(Level.TRACE, Level.INFO, Level.ERROR);\\\\n            assertThat(events).extracting(LoggingEvent::getRenderedMessage)\\\\n                    .containsExactly(\\\\\\\"trace message\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"info first second\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"error message\\\\\\\");\\\\n            assertThat(events).extracting(LoggingEvent::getLoggerName)\\\\n                    .containsOnly(\\\\\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-standard\\\\\\\");\\\\n            assertThat(events.get(2).getThrowableInformation().getThrowable()).isSameAs(failure);\\\\n        }\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void locationAwareLoggingMapsSlf4jLevelsToLog4jLevels() {\\\\n        try (TestLoggerContext context = TestLoggerContext.create(\\\\\\\"slf4j-log4j12-adapter-location-aware\\\\\\\")) {\\\\n            LocationAwareLogger logger = (LocationAwareLogger) context.slf4jLogger();\\\\n            IllegalArgumentException failure = new IllegalArgumentException(\\\\\\\"warn\\\\\\\");\\\\n\\\\n            logger.log(null, LocationAwareInvoker.class.getName(), LocationAwareLogger.WARN_INT,\\\\n                    \\\\\\\"warn message\\\\\\\", null, failure);\\\\n\\\\n            assertThat(context.events()).singleElement().satisfies(event -> {\\\\n                assertThat(event.getLevel()).isEqualTo(Level.WARN);\\\\n                assertThat(event.getRenderedMessage()).isEqualTo(\\\\\\\"warn message\\\\\\\");\\\\n                assertThat(event.getThrowableInformation().getThrowable()).isSameAs(failure);\\\\n                assertThat(event.getFQNOfLoggerClass()).isEqualTo(LocationAwareInvoker.class.getName());\\\\n            });\\\\n        }\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static final class TestLoggerContext implements AutoCloseable {\\\\n\\\\n        private final org.apache.log4j.Logger log4jLogger;\\\\n        private final Level previousLevel;\\\\n        private final boolean previousAdditivity;\\\\n        private final List<Appender> previousAppenders;\\\\n        private final RecordingAppender appender;\\\\n        private final org.slf4j.Logger slf4jLogger;\\\\n\\\\n        private TestLoggerContext(String loggerName) {\\\\n            this.log4jLogger = LogManager.getLogger(loggerName);\\\\n            this.previousLevel = this.log4jLogger.getLevel();\\\\n            this.previousAdditivity = this.log4jLogger.getAdditivity();\\\\n            this.previousAppenders = currentAppenders(this.log4jLogger);\\\\n            this.appender = new RecordingAppender();\\\\n\\\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAllAppenders();\\\\n            this.log4jLogger.setAdditivity(false);\\\\n            this.log4jLogger.setLevel(Level.TRACE);\\\\n            this.log4jLogger.addAppender(this.appender);\\\\n            this.slf4jLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(loggerName);\\\\n        }\\\\n\\\\n        private static TestLoggerContext create(String loggerName) {\\\\n            return new Tes